gdom","Great Hyde Hall, Sawbridgeworth, Hertfordshire, England":"Sawbridgeworth, Hertfordshire, England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Liston","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English: habitational name from a place in Essex, so named from the Old English personal name <i>Lissa</i> (probably a pet form of <i>Lēofsige</i>, from <i>lēof</i> ‘dear, beloved’ + <i>sige</i> ‘victory’) + <i>tūn</i> ‘enclosure, settlement’.","Scottish: habitational name from any of the places in West Lothian and Midlothian, which probably have the same origin as in 1 above. This surname is also found in Ireland.","Irish: Anglo-Norman name which has been in Limerick since the 13th century, originally <i>de Lexinton</i>, so presumably a habitational name from Lexington in Essex."],"variants":[]},{"name":"Alice","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Originally a variant of   Adelaide  , representing an Old French spelling of a reduced form of Germanic <i>Adalheidis</i>. <i>Alice</i> and <i>Adelaide</i> were already regarded as distinct names in English during the medieval period. <i>Alice</i> enjoyed a surge of popularity in the 19th century and periods of favour ever since. It was the name of the central character of  Lewis Carroll's  Alice's Adventures in Wonderland (  1865 ) and Through the Looking Glass (  1872 ), who was based on his child friend  Alice Liddell , daughter of the Dean of Christ Church, Oxford."],"variants":[{"name":"Alys","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Alice ."]},{"name":"Alis","meanings":["equivalent of <b>Alice</b> ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Alice Liston was born about 1253, in England, United Kingdom as the daughter of William Liston. She married Thomas Josselyn about 1272, in Sawbridgeworth, Hertfordshire, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 2 sons. She died in 1275, in Sawbridgew